      "writtenOn": "2026-03-02T13:06:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Well, that\u0027s normal and shouldn\u0027t be mentioned anyway. The issue isn\u0027t bypassing the submit requirements, code-review approvals or CI checks, that\u0027s exactly the `submit` permission on `refs/for/\u003c\u003e` ref. The issue here is that the `submit` permission is automatically granted even if the caller does not have any rights on the other changes that belong to the same topic.",
